<subSubSection id="204C9910B23B812679905711FCD8A7F0" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="29D00DD028A34C13DF4C899B6CA5E683" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A272F7FFF0D4CC387C58C43F91113D3D" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Wings pale grey, finely peppered with brown fuscous species, externally easily mixed with 
<taxonomicName id="C24E3A983CE7DDEB2FB571FC02A44087" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. manchaoensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manchaoensis">
<emphasis id="615A1F7633B5408814448D082D076F6A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">S. manchaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but separated by fringes being distinctly darker than forewing (same colour as forewing in 
<taxonomicName id="47647D922F015DFE8FFA374598F2322A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. manchaoensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manchaoensis">
<emphasis id="84695D5916A2ADEEE804D4AE2A7AC6B4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">S. manchaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and absence of small spot at cell end (present in 
<taxonomicName id="AA287C2D85AEA4602C72CEAA80CD663E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. manchaoensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manchaoensis">
<emphasis id="97DE494419F1428C968B4774F0F07342" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">S. manchaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In the female genitalia, a large and distinctly defined oval sterigma is diagnostic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7FE5A21A6AEB53C261DF0D7A938588C5" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph id="292B49944680ADACC6E68CD0AD9FBAF5" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D54B6E53C0967AC14FF2312B2740921B" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Wingspan 15-18 mm. Head, collar, neck tuft, haustellum, tegula and thorax fuscous, same colour as forewing, head and haustellum mixed with dirty white. Scape fuscous except ventral surface and pecten whitish grey, pectin longer than diameter of scape. Flagellum fuscous, 0.6 
<normalizedToken id="D5A2D3FA6C2EB47CA9D7D8C6F74059B7" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of forewing. Labial palp: palpomere I pale dirty white; palpomeres II and III: upper surface dirty white, otherwise fuscous mixed with a few dirty white scales. Legs fuscous, mixed with dirty white. Abdomen dorsally pale fuscous, ventrally dirty white. Forewing pale grey, finely peppered with brown, fringes darker than wing. Hindwing slightly paler than forewing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0ADA20733E9D3DB5E74001F3220987BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="DEACD1EA975595D69EBDAF916D7C2C65" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="B6A0394BF02FEB45D1200EC5C7885FA6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Female genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Sterigma oval ring with sclerotised margin, anteriorly with quadrangular sclerotised extension. Ostium situated anteriorly in ring. Sternum VII quadrangular; posterior margin medially incurved, anterior margin sclerotised. Apophyses anteriores 0.5 
<normalizedToken id="08FC5488C1F44C703A489799081D1F4D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of apophyses posteriores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="66AAE9B1082A5C1CF141C0B985D82A68" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="6408DE8B2729EF07584E4E931493D4D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9DC8AC100DF26BE62AA15580F05FB1D1" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Latinised adjective in the nominative singular. The species is named after the type locality, the Salinas Grandes salt lake.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="85047F93D053DF88DA323E83E2BCC21A" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F28E9D107832BB93E50C6386511EC148" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E2E49191AD74B8272D31716F6051674D" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">NW Argentina.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="749FE45463F518D9AED14D3F8710A951" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="30CAAACDBE1FBB0468C6C071EBD78CE1" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="67C005EDE7BB5F9D02B3B72F935DB0E5" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">The collecting site is the shore of a large salt lake, in the zone between a dry shrubby area and low halophytic vegetation.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="588A394BAA11F6FD1B46E908F64807CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="genetic data">
<paragraph id="EBD7BF13DF82514F30685B400DEC5ED9" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Genetic data.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="070575DCBA1B7AA5C26249E7493D36A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
BIN: BOLD:ADY7738 (
<emphasis id="DEDBC7C705DD35C4AA4EAB4924482101" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">n</emphasis>
= 2 from Argentina). Nearest neighbour: 
<taxonomicName id="5DBB7A58C723AE996D5C53AC5FDF4A1C" authorityName="Nupponen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris furciphallella" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furciphallella">
<emphasis id="3CED748E2CAA7D479B4FAF6B4DD15111" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris furciphallella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nupponen, sp. nov. (BIN: BOLD:ADY9699, 4.49%). 
<taxonomicName id="73A6F005F64382A586907CA77882EF9A" authorityName="Nupponen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris manchaoensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manchaoensis">
<emphasis id="D0FCC927232FE04FC43BDE3B056F08D3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris manchaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is externally similar, and its barcode differs by 5.62%.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9DCE84B7261A899D52F17BAEF8AD498C" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="A06EF0F336AC8CF376D33993AB31B2B6" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DC697C6E9AA58356BCC2BB89860AA37B" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">
Male unknown. Based on COI maximum likelihood phylogeny, South American taxa 
<taxonomicName id="D0CEB698E9A008A65F18F08F4AF9FD4F" authorityName="Nupponen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris salinasgrandensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salinasgrandensis">
<emphasis id="FD23B5A7E3DDF5D9B5EF337D1776E880" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris salinasgrandensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F4E2C2BDD3F2257F3CE5A744E7772995" authorityName="Nupponen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris furciphallella" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furciphallella">
<emphasis id="614938BA824D4706919BAB0F5ED7D8AC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris furciphallella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="88970D97387334920BDF53CBF5E38C15" authorityName="Nupponen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris manchaoensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manchaoensis">
<emphasis id="B6A32087379AE3CA2D65FB07DD43AAC3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris manchaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F14940F4B7F62B4C72B064C1C4670890" authorityName="Nupponen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris angustivalvella" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustivalvella">
<emphasis id="00E825E13B9EBF829F10BAB379668EFB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris angustivalvella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4B4FA9E145F1F5D307EA1D5EA67467A9" authorityName="Nupponen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris directiphallella" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="directiphallella">
<emphasis id="F7074C0CF51431BF7ED810A71585B41C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris directiphallella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group together, associating within a clade, whose taxa are classified in apparently non-monophyletic 
<taxonomicName id="97242F9052BF8DB3E7D1D87E489FE6B2" authorityName="Nupponen 1 &amp; Sihvonen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9D10A55C3E92F0B4F605DF7EEA1A3713" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on BOLD (Suppl. material 2). We classify these taxa in 
<taxonomicName id="1B1E10D9B0822CAEDA737BA0356B4383" authorityName="Nupponen 1 &amp; Sihvonen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="25AD60A91C840BBBFD3EAC2638A56D5D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
